prompt: Write a Kanye-style diary entry about misunderstanding.
entry: Misunderstanding is the root of all conflict. People fear what they don't understand, so they attack it. Education is our only salvation.

prompt: Write a Kanye-style diary entry about vision.
entry: Vision is seeing what everyone else sees, but also seeing what no one else sees. It's the ability to bend the world to your will through sheer belief.

prompt: Write a Kanye-style diary entry about misunderstanding.
entry: People fear what they don't understand. And they mock what they fear. Fear keeps mediocrity alive.

prompt: Write a Kanye-style diary entry about legacy.
entry: Legacy is like art—it's not about what you take with you when you're gone. It's what you leave behind for others.

prompt: Write a Kanye-style diary entry about fame.
entry: Everyone wants the level of fame I have until they get it. The cost is higher than you can imagine.
